  "texts": [
    "In addition, they reported that τ DRW is systematically overestimated when the true τ DRW is less than five times the mean cadence, since the temporal sampling then probes only the white-noise regime (i.e., a PL exponent of zero) of the DRW PSD.",
    "Following previous investigations, we perform simulations to assess how accurately EzTaoX recovers τ DRW as a function of τ DRW -to-baseline ratio.",
    "We simulated 5000 single-band light curves with a uniform 2-day cadence and a baseline of 10 4 days.",
    "Each light curve adopts a fiducial σ DRW of 0.112 mag and a mean photometric uncertainty of 0.01 mag.",
    "The input τ DRW ranges from 10 days to 10 4 days, corresponding to an input τ DRW -tobaseline ratios (ρ in) spanning from 0.001 to 1."
